*[[1940]] &amp;ndash; [[Walter Chrysler]], American businessman, founded [[Chrysler]] (b. 1875)
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; [[Rafaela Ottiano]], Italian-American actress (b. 1888)
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; [[Ali-Agha Shikhlinski]], Russian-Azerbaijani general (b. 1865)
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[Ernst Thälmann]], German politician (b. 1886)
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Subhas Chandra Bose]], Indian independence leader (b. 1897)
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul Mares]], American trumpet player and bandleader ([[New Orleans Rhythm Kings]]) (b. 1900)
*[[1950]] &amp;ndash; [[Julien Lahaut]], Belgian politician (b. 1884)
*[[1952]] &amp;ndash; [[Alberto Hurtado]], Chilean priest, lawyer, writer, and saint (b. 1901)
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; [[Clifford Odets]], American playwright (b. 1906)
*[[1968]] &amp;ndash; [[Cy Walter]], American pianist (b. 1915)
*[[1970]] &amp;ndash; [[Soledad Miranda]], Spanish actress (b. 1943)
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[Anita Loos]], American screenwriter and author (b. 1889)
*[[1983]] &amp;ndash; [[Nikolaus Pevsner]], German-English historian (b. 1902)
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Grethe and Jørgen Ingmann|Grethe Ingmann]], Danish singer (b. 1938)
*  1990   &amp;ndash; [[B. F. Skinner]], American psychologist, invented the [[Skinner box]] (b. 1904)
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; [[Christopher McCandless]], American adventurer (b. 1968)
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; [[Martin Cahill]], Irish criminal (b. 1949)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Nelly's]], Greek photographer (b. 1899)
*  1998   &amp;ndash; [[Persis Khambatta]], Indian actress (b. 1950)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[David Peakall]], English scientist (b. 1931)
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; [[Dean Riesner]], American screenwriter (b. 1918)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Tony Jackson (bass player)|Tony Jackson]], English singer and bass player ([[The Searchers (band)|The Searchers]]) (b. 1938)
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Elmer Bernstein]], American composer (b. 1922)
*  2004   &amp;ndash; [[Hiram Fong]], American politician (b. 1906)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Christopher Bauman]], American wrestler (b. 1982)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Gao Xiumin (actress)|Gao Xiumin]], Chinese actress (b. 1959)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[George Astaphan]], Caribbean physician (b. 1946)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Fernand Gignac]], Canadian singer and actor (b. 1934)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Michael Deaver]], American politician (b. 1938)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Kim Dae-jung]], South Korean politician, 15th [[President of South Korea]], [[Nobel Peace Prize|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1925)
*  2009   &amp;ndash; [[Rose Friedman]], American economist (b. 1910)
*  2009   &amp;ndash; [[Robert Novak]], American journalist (b. 1931)
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[Hal Connolly]], American hammer thrower (b. 1931)
*  2010   &amp;ndash; [[Scott Davis (announcer)|Scott Davis]], American sportscaster (b. 1943)
*  2010   &amp;ndash; [[Benjamin Kaplan]], American scholar and jurist (b. 1911)
*[[2012]] &amp;ndash; [[Hisham al-Hayali]], Iraqi politician
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Tayseer al-Mashhadani]], Iraqi engineer and politician
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[John Lynch-Staunton]], Canadian politician (b. 1930)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Scott McKenzie]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (b. 1939)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Ra. Ki. Rangarajan]], Indian journalist and author (b. 1927)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Jesse Robredo]], Filipino politician (b. 1958)
